docs.abstract: In a rare move, French authorities charged Lafarge SA, one of France’s biggest companies, with financing the Islamic State and endangering the lives of its employees.
docs.snippet: In a rare move, French authorities charged Lafarge SA, one of France’s biggest companies, with financing the Islamic State and endangering the lives of its employees.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — One of France’s biggest companies was placed under formal investigation on Thursday over allegations that it financed terrorist groups, including the Islamic State, and aided and abetted crimes against humanity in a bid to continue operating in Syria as a civil war raged there.

headline.main: French Cement Giant Lafarge Indicted on Terror Financing Charge in Syria

docs.abstract: As Beijing encourages its corporate sector to buy up the technology to build its own national champions, Britain is joining other countries in applying a microscope to such deals.
docs.snippet: As Beijing encourages its corporate sector to buy up the technology to build its own national champions, Britain is joining other countries in applying a microscope to such deals.
docs.lead_paragraph: Britain on Tuesday joined a growing group of Western nations hardening their use of national security as a litmus test for Chinese investments, with the government in London unveiling a  blueprint to sharply tighten its oversight of foreign takeovers.

headline.main: Its Eye on China, Britain Pushes Back on Foreign Takeovers
headline.print_headline: Wary of Chinese Takeovers, Britain Tightens Oversight

docs.abstract: In his latest salvo in a battle to reform the Swiss conglomerate, Mr. Loeb criticized the board for acting too slowly and urged it to split the company in three.

headline.print_headline: Loeb Pushes to Pry Nestlé  Into a Three-Way Split

docs.abstract: An executive at the giant retailer signed a document that indicated the property was being purchased with a loan from a large shelter operator.
docs.snippet: An executive at the giant retailer signed a document that indicated the property was being purchased with a loan from a large shelter operator.
docs.lead_paragraph: Walmart said it was “surprised and deeply disturbed” to learn that one of its former Texas stores was being used to house migrant children who had been separated from their parents. “We sold the building in 2016 to a developer and had no knowledge then of its intended use today,” the giant retailer said in a Twitter post last week.

headline.main: Walmart ‘Surprised’ Old Store Is a Migrant Shelter. Records Hinted at the Possibility.
headline.print_headline: Walmart Sold Texas Store To Buyer Tied to Shelters
